<h2 class="sectionedit3" id="development_tasksopenwrt_improvements">Development Tasks / OpenWrt improvements</h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
read <a href="https://dev.openwrt.org/wiki/SubmittingPatches" class="urlextern" title="https://dev.openwrt.org/wiki/SubmittingPatches"  rel="nofollow">https://dev.openwrt.org/wiki/SubmittingPatches</a> and <a href="devel/patches#editanexistingpatch" class="wikilink1" title="doc:devel:patches">edit.an.existing.patch</a>
</p>
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> fix OpenWrt bugs on official bug tracker <a href="https://dev.openwrt.org/report/1?sort=created&amp;asc=0&amp;page=1" class="urlextern" title="https://dev.openwrt.org/report/1?sort=created&amp;asc=0&amp;page=1"  rel="nofollow">Open Tickets</a></div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> fix packages feeds issues: <a href="https://github.com/openwrt/packages/issues" class="urlextern" title="https://github.com/openwrt/packages/issues"  rel="nofollow">open issues</a></div>
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Webinterface / Luci2 / other Proof of Concepts</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Replace ifconfig busybox with iproute2 (rejected atm for possible size increase)</div>
</li>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> Replace ifconfig with busybox ip</div>
</li>
</ul>
<div class="plugin_wrap"><ul>
<li class="level1"><div class="li"> replace <strong><code>ifconfig</code></strong> (i.e. <code>busybox-ifconfig</code>) with <strong><code>ip</code></strong> (i.e. <code>busybox-ip</code>) or with <strong><code>uci</code></strong> in OpenWrt-scripts</div>
<ol>
<li class="level2"><div class="li"> Read <a href="http://blog.timheckman.net/2011/12/22/why-you-should-replace-ifconfig/" class="urlextern" title="http://blog.timheckman.net/2011/12/22/why-you-should-replace-ifconfig/"  rel="nofollow">Why ip instead of ifconfig</a> and <a href="uci.1#commandlineutility" class="wikilink1" title="doc:uci">why uci instead of grep/awk/sed</a></div>
</li>
<li class="level2"><div class="li"> differences in invocation <a href="http://www.tty1.net/blog/2010-04-21-ifconfig-ip-comparison_en.html" class="urlextern" title="http://www.tty1.net/blog/2010-04-21-ifconfig-ip-comparison_en.html"  rel="nofollow">http://www.tty1.net/blog/2010-04-21-ifconfig-ip-comparison_en.html</a> and also in the output</div>
</li>
<li class="level2"><div class="li"> How?</div>
<ol>
<li class="level3"><div class="li"> <a href="howto/buildroot.exigence" class="wikilink1" title="doc:howto:buildroot.exigence">buildroot.exigence</a></div>
</li>
<li class="level3"><div class="li"> search in files and subfolders for the invocation of ifconfig, e.g. <code>grep -r &quot;ifconfig&quot; ~/openwrt/trunk</code> or <code>grep -r &quot;ifconfig&quot; * | grep dropbear&quot; the later giving&lt;code&gt;
package/network/services/dropbear/files/.svn/text-base/dropbear.init.svn-base:			ifconfig &quot;$ifname&quot; | sed -ne &#039;
package/network/services/dropbear/files/dropbear.init:			ifconfig &quot;$ifname&quot; | sed -ne &#039;&lt;/code&gt;
    - edit </code>package/network/services/dropbear/files/dropbear.init<code> and replace ifconfig with ip or with uci
    - edit </code>package/base-files/files/lib/preinit/10_indicate_preinit&#039;&#039; and replace ifconfig with ip</div>
</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

